						<summary>

						

						<p>On three faces of a pillar lying in the verandah in front of the Agastyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in archaic characters is undated.</p>						

						<p>It mentions Vallava Saḷki, his son Hari Rāchapaṟu whose son was Paṇḍaya at whose request some grant seems to have been made at Chiṟuburu.</p>						

						</summary>
